# Premises:
Cost(GRE, 205USD) ::: The GRE test has a cost of $205 USD.
∀x (GREApplicant(x) ∧ Prove(x, EconomicHardship) → Provides(ETS, FinancialAid, x)) ::: ETS provides financial aid to any GRE applicant who proves economic hardship.

Person(tom) ::: Tom is a person.
LivesIn(tom, SingleParentFamily) ::: Tom lives in a single-parent family.
∃y (Dad(y, tom) ∧ OutOfWork(y, Year(year_more_than_one))) ::: Tom has a dad who has been out of work for over a year.

# Conclusion:
Cost(GRE_Test, 205) ∧ (205 < 300)

HavingTooLittleMoney(tom). # Tom is experiencing having too little money.
Difficulty(tom). # Having too little money is a difficulty.

# Based on the above, Tom experiences economic hardship.
EconomicHardship(tom).

# Tom proves economic hardship. This is a necessary condition for receiving aid,

Prove(tom, EconomicHardship).
